<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing seat covers can dramatically enhance the appearance and functionality of your Jeep's interior, particularly when it comes to protecting leather seats from wear and tear. In this article, we'll focus on the installation of Bartact's Tactical Bench Seat Covers, specifically designed for the 2018-19 Jeep Wrangler JL with leather seats that feature a rear fold-down armrest. This installation is straightforward, but knowing the nuances will make the entire process smoother.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This guide will walk you through the installation process for the Bartact rear seat covers. We'll highlight important considerations and challenges to keep in mind to ensure a successful installation. While the specific focus is on models with leather seating, those with cloth seats can still apply these steps with minor adjustments.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Pre-Installation Preparation</strong>: Before you start installing, familiarize yourself with the layout of your Jeep's rear seats. For the 2018 JL with leather seats, the installation will involve working around a rear center console that houses cupholders and the fold-down armrest.</li><li><strong>Remove Existing Covers and Mats</strong>: Start by removing any existing seat covers or accessories from the rear seats. If you have optional floor mats, take those out as well; they'll only get in the way during installation.</li><li><strong>Install the Bottom Cover</strong>: Begin by loosening the velcro on the bottom of the seat cover and slide it over the top of the seat. Note the location of the MOLLE pouch that is designed to fit behind the center console. Make sure the console is in the upright position as you tuck the cover into place.</li><li><strong>Secure the Cover</strong>: Apply the velcro around the seat's base to firmly attach the cover. Make sure everything is smoothed out, as a snug fit not only looks better but ensures durability.</li><li><strong>Work with the Headrests</strong>: Depending on the design, you may need to remove some headrests before sliding on the seat cover. Bartact's covers include slots and attachments designed for this purpose. Once the cover fits over the seat, replace the headrests, ensuring they tuck under appropriately.</li><li><strong>Final Adjustments</strong>: Make any last-hand adjustments to ensure the cover is neat and secure. This step includes tucking in excess fabric and ensuring all velcro sections are properly attached.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Ensure you have the right tools at hand, particularly an 18mm socket wrench for seat belt attachments.</li><li>Don’t rush the installation—taking your time will lead to a better finish and prevent frustration.</li><li>If you're struggling, don't hesitate to refer back to the manufacturer's instructions or installation video for guidance.</li><li>Consider having a buddy help you; an extra set of hands can make handling the seat covers easier, especially when managing the fit around the center console.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing Bartact's rear seat covers in a 2018 Jeep Wrangler JL is a practical mod that protects your seats while enhancing the interior aesthetics. With some patience and the right approach, you'll have a snug fit that keeps your seats looking fresh and ready for any adventure. Remember, while this installation may seem daunting at first, the satisfaction and protection it provides are well worth the effort.</p>

